 POSTDOCTORAL ASSOCIATE ,  Media Lab , to join a highly collaborative team of learning designers, developers, researchers, faculty, and students developing an inclusive artificial intelligence (AI) literacy curriculum for middle school in collaboration with schools in the U.S., the UAE and other countries worldwide, ensuring that it supports a diversity of learner interests and needs. Responsibilities include designing experimental project-based learning units in AI using student-centered methodologies; investigating educational tools and platforms with both established and emerging AI and pedagogy domain expertise; devising thought leadership-in concert with principal investigators-around artificial intelligence and machine learning education to research teams by providing technical consultations, literature reviews, conference participation, training, and (MIT) student and staff guidance; researching and implementing studies of pedagogical approaches to support younger learners (K-12) in a variety of contexts, including special needs learners; and conducting fieldwork with K-12 teachers, administrators, students, and parents at collaborator locations worldwide (mostly online during pandemic).
 
 
A full job description is available at https://www.media.mit.edu/about/job-opportunities/ 
 
 Job Requirements 
 REQUIRED : Ph..D in computer science or scientific or engineering field with focus on computation; experience teaching K-12 students and developing STEM learning experiences as part of their academic training; broad technical knowledge of a wide varietyof current AI and ML research and practice; technical experience with implementation of AI or ML tools/models/artifacts; and familiarly with open-source philosophy and methodologies.  PREFERRED : comprehensive understanding of the design thinking process; and experience with Tensorflow, Pytorch, or other ML libraries.  Job #19628 
 
This is a temporary appointment through June 30, 2022, but will be considered for renewal pending long-term funding. MIT 6 days ago original job Report job Apply Now Apply On Company Site Save this job Save this job Post-doctoral Fellow jobs in Cambridge, MA Jobs at MIT in Cambridge, MA Post-doctoral Fellow salaries in Cambridge, MA Company Info Follow Get job updates from MIT MIT 374 reviews The Massachusetts Institute of Technology (MIT) is a private research university in Cambridge, Massachusetts. Founded in 1861 in response... Let employers find you Thousands of employers search for candidates on Indeed Upload your resume Hiring Lab Career Advice Browse Jobs Browse Companies Salaries Find Certifications Indeed Events Work at Indeed Countries About Help Center Â© 2021 Indeed Do Not Sell My Personal Information Accessibility at Indeed Privacy Center Cookies Privacy Terms Let Employers Find You Upload Your Resume 
 
 
 
 
 
